iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Wildlife vets were trying to take a snare off a lion in western Zimbabwe but the rescue mission nearly went terribly wrong.Harare - A day-old baby was reportedly rescued by good Samaritans a few weeks ago after being dumped in St Mary's, Chitungwiza outside of Harare, Zimbabwe.According to The Sunday Mail, the infant was found wrapped in a T-shirt and soaked in rainwater. The baby's mother Mavis Kasirai, 18, gave birth to the infant on January 9 before "dumping the baby in rainwater a day later". The baby was discovered by Mathias Tivaone while on his way to church. He had heard the baby crying in a grassy area near a car park.Mathias&nbsp;alerted his mother Catharine Tivaone, who rushed the baby to the hospital.Kasirai was sentenced to 10 months in prison after she pleaded guilty to exposing an infant to danger.Around the same time last year, a 5-day-old baby boy was dumped by his 26-year-old mother at a grave yard in Waterfalls, Harare, according to Zimbabwe Daily.Mercy Madziwa allegedly tied the baby's neck with a T-shirt, placed it in a plastic bag, before dumping it at a cemetery.&nbsp;Madziwa pleaded guilty to the charge of child negligence. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.